# CSS Syntax

## Basic Structure

```css
selector {
    property: value;
}
```

## Example

```css
h1 {
    color: blue;
    font-size: 30px;
}
```

### Explanation

- h1 → Selector
- color → Property
- blue → Value
- font-size → Property
- 30px → Value

## Multiple Properties

```css
p {
    color: black;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.5;
}
```

## Best Practices

- Use proper indentation
- End every property with semicolon
- Use meaningful class names

## Summary

CSS syntax follows the pattern:

Selector → Property → Value
